name: Jin Yao Xuan Specialty Restaurant
description: Enjoy local flavors in a modern Chinese ambiance at Jin Yao Xuan. Stretching from the 53rd to the 54th floor—with the floors connected by a grand staircase and internal lift—this entrancing restaurant presents bird’s-eye city and river views through glass walls or outdoors, on the 54th floor. A glass pool adds to the contemporary setting, providing a semi-outdoor dining experience. The pool is also visible from the 53rd floor through glass flooring, which extends to the viewing deck. The breathtaking setting is matched only by the enticing cuisine, which unites a passion for the freshest seafood—flown in daily—with traditional Chongqing hotpot. Indulge in locally inspired, epicurean specialties, like Cantonese abalone stew, lobster, and fresh organic mushrooms, or opt for gourmet meat options, such as 4A-grade marbled beef slices and handmade meatballs. There is a private dining area on the 54th floor, which can be portioned for privacy and seats up to ten guests. Reservations are recommended for private dining.
